---
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import Card from "../components/card/Card.astro";
import PageLink from "../components/page-link/PageLink.astro";

import trustyPic from "../images/Trusty-Loading-screen.png";
import lavenderTeaPic from "../images/Lavender-tea.png";
import Link from "../components/link/Link.astro";
import Tag from "../components/tag/Tag.astro";
---

<div class="flex flex-col gap-4">
  <Card title="Bloom co.">
    <div class="flex flex-row gap-2">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 justify-between">
        <div>
          <p>
            Tea is often seen as old-fashioned and boring. How can we make tea
            more appealing to Gen-Z consumers? And how can we refresh the
            branding of packaged tea?
            <br />
            <br />
            Meet Bloom co.â€”a contemporary tea brand that gives tea a modern, vibrant
            twist. Our rebranding focuses on eye-catching visuals in both the website
            and packaging, making it fun and engaging for Gen-Z consumers to explore
            and purchase their perfect tea.
            <br />
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-row gap-2 pt-2">
            <Tag>User research</Tag>
            <Tag>Prototyping</Tag>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-row flex-wrap gap-4">
          <PageLink
            aria-label="View Tea project case study (opens a new window)"
            href="https://www.figma.com/deck/al0HIY4mxXvO71nXE3wvhV/Bloom-co.-Tea?node-id=1-25&t=5bJp7x1FheuLZYYK-1"
            newTab
            >View case study<Icon name="up-right-from-square" />
          </PageLink>
          <Link
            aria-label="See Tea project prototype (opens a new window)"
            href="https://www.figma.com/proto/tY7e1uZKMTqGAiQvO6gKKt/Tea%3A-Nikolette%2C-Emma%2C-Caroline%2C-and-Orion?node-id=683-1137&node-type=frame&t=KKeLkya1sN9rkLPo-1&scaling=min-zoom&content-scaling=fixed&page-id=1%3A4"
            newTab
            underline
            >See prototype <Icon name="up-right-from-square" />
          </Link>
        </div>
      </div>
      <Image
        class="rounded-2xl m-1 object-cover hidden sm:block"
        src={lavenderTeaPic}
        alt="Bloom co. tea thumbnail"
        width={200}
        quality={100}
      />
    </div>
  </Card>
  <Card title="Trusty">
    <div class="flex flex-row gap-2">
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 justify-between">
        <div>
          <p>
            How do we design a news app that is trustworthy and unbiased? How
            can we reduce users' mental load while seeing news from all over the
            world? We created a user-friendly app experience that focused on
            transparency in news sourcing, making it easy for users to verify
            the credibility of information directly within the app interface.
            <br />
            <br />
            As our first Creative Jam, we receive an honorable mention,
            placing in the top 20 out of 315 teams in the competition!
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-row gap-2 pt-2">
            <Tag>UI design</Tag>
            <Tag>Prototyping</Tag>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-row flex-wrap gap-4">
          <PageLink href="/ux-projects/trusty"
            >View case study<Icon
              name="arrow-right-long"
              class="page-link-icon"
            />
          </PageLink>
          <Link
            aria-label="See Trusty prototype (opens a new window)"
            href="https://xd.adobe.com/view/3e5904f8-347a-412f-9f67-bb6cd05324f1-6b0a/"
            newTab
            underline
            >See prototype <Icon name="up-right-from-square" />
          </Link>
        </div>
      </div>
      <Image
        class="rounded-2xl m-1 object-cover hidden sm:block"
        src={trustyPic}
        alt="Trusty app thumbnail"
        width={200}
        quality={100}
      />
    </div>
  </Card>
</div>
